      • queryExecGETJSON

        @GET
 @Produces(value="application/json")
public javax.ws.rs.core.Response queryExecGETJSON(@DefaultValue(value="application/json") @QueryParam(value="format")
                                                                                              String f,
                                                                                              @QueryParam(value="query")
                                                                                              String q,
                                                                                              @DefaultValue(value="") @QueryParam(value="token")
                                                                                              String token)
                                                                                       throws IOException
        GET service which executes a SPARQL query and returns the results in various formats. The query is applied on a default namespace defined in the configuration file.
        URL: /ld-services/query?query={query1}&format={format1}
        Parameters:
        query - Query parameter which has a string value representing the SPARQL query which will be applied.
        format - Query parameter which refers on the requested mimetype-format of the results. The formats which are supported are: text/csv, application/json, text/tab-separated-values, application/sparql-results+xml.
        Returns:
        A Response instance which has an entity content with the query results and the required format.
        Throws:
        IOException

        GET service which executes a SPARQL query and returns the results in various formats. The query is applied on a namespace provided as a path parameter.
        URL: /ld-services/query/namespace/{namespace}?query={query1}&format={format1}
        Parameters:
        namespace - Path parameter which denotes the namespace in which the query will be applied.
        f - Query parameter which refers on the requested mimetype-format of the results. The formats which are supported are: text/csv, application/json, text/tab-separated-values, application/sparql-results+xml.
        q - Query parameter which has a string value representing the SPARQL query which will be applied.
        Returns:
        A Response instance which has an entity content with the query results and the required format.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedEncodingException
        IOException

        @POST
 @Consumes(value="application/json")
public javax.ws.rs.core.Response queryExecPOSTJSON(String jsonInput,
                                                                                                @DefaultValue(value="") @QueryParam(value="token")
                                                                                                String token)
                                                                                         throws IOException,
                                                                                                org.json.simple.parser.ParseException
        POST service which executes a SPARQL query and returns the results in various formats. The query is applied on a default namespace defined in the configuration file.
        URL: /ld-services/query
        Parameters:
        jsonInput - A JSON-encoded string which has the following form:
        {
        "query" : "select ?s ?p ...",
        "format" : "text/csv"
        }
        where
        • query - A string which represents the SPARQL query which will be applied.
        • format - The format(MIME type) of the query results. text/csv, application/json, text/tab-separated-values, application/sparql-results+xml.
        Returns:
        A Response instance which has a JSON-encoded entity content with the query results in the requested format.
        Throws:
        IOException
        org.json.simple.parser.ParseException
